git restore to restore "modified" file to when it was last staged.
when you have text1 in staged area and text2 in modified state, but you want to commit text2 first: git restore --staged takes text1 back to the modified area.
git commit -a (add+commit)
git rm notes.txt 
you must select one of the below options
cached: retain the file in the working area
force: delete the file permanently
